Distribution. At present this species is known only from the vicinity of the type locality, Hampi—a World Heritage Site located in Bellary district of Karnataka, India (
Fig. 4
). This species was observed to be relatively common at the locality, with sightings in the all the temple ruins in the Hampi and Kamlapur areas.
